{ wp_event_id: 443603477540769488 id: "c1426239" message/content[0]/text: "🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — We ship features faster than Apple ships calculator updates.\n\nUsage: openclaw models [options] [command]\n\nModel discovery, scanning, and configuration\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>     Agent id to inspect (overrides\n                   OPENCLAW_AGENT_DIR/PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR)\n  -h, --help       Display help for command\n  --status-json    Output JSON (alias for `models status --json`) (default:\n                   false)\n  --status-plain   Plain output (alias for `models status --plain`) (default:\n                   false)\n\nCommands:\n  aliases          Manage model aliases\n  auth             Manage model auth profiles\n  fallbacks        Manage model fallback list\n  image-fallbacks  Manage image model fallback list\n  list             List models (configured by default)\n  scan             Scan OpenRouter free models for tools + images\n  set              Set the default model\n  set-image        Set the image model\n  status           Show configured model state\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/models" message/content[0]/type: "text" message/details/aggregated: "🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — We ship features faster than Apple ships calculator updates.\n\nUsage: openclaw models [options] [command]\n\nModel discovery, scanning, and configuration\n\nOptions:\n  --agent <id>     Agent id to inspect (overrides\n                   OPENCLAW_AGENT_DIR/PI_CODING_AGENT_DIR)\n  -h, --help       Display help for command\n  --status-json    Output JSON (alias for `models status --json`) (default:\n                   false)\n  --status-plain   Plain output (alias for `models status --plain`) (default:\n                   false)\n\nCommands:\n  aliases          Manage model aliases\n  auth             Manage model auth profiles\n  fallbacks        Manage model fallback list\n  image-fallbacks  Manage image model fallback list\n  list             List models (configured by default)\n  scan             Scan OpenRouter free models for tools + images\n  set              Set the default model\n  set-image        Set the image model\n  status           Show configured model state\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/models" message/details/cwd: "/Users/zuowenjian/.openclaw/workspace" message/details/durationMs: 757 message/details/exitCode: 0 message/details/status: "completed" message/isError: false message/role: "toolResult" message/timestamp: 1773799758284 message/toolCallId: "tool_nbPIVWVsUF74RCtSJXuz9n3x" message/toolName: "exec" parentId: "c786c3b0" timestamp: "2026-03-18T02:09:18.285Z" type: "message" wp_src_key: "file_1" access_source: "../openclaw/target_data/raw_log.dat" }
{ wp_event_id: 443603477540769489 id: "6f061cea" message/api: "anthropic-messages" message/content[0]/thinking: "没有看到直接的 usage/cost 命令。让我查看 session 相关的命令，或者查看是否有 `openclaw usage` 或 `openclaw cost` 命令。" message/content[0]/thinkingSignature: "" message/content[0]/type: "thinking" message/content[1]/arguments/command: "openclaw --help 2>&1 | head -50" message/content[1]/id: "tool_k03eV85usHu4Nijw70TBfIKD" message/content[1]/name: "exec" message/content[1]/type: "toolCall" message/model: "k2p5" message/provider: "kimi-coding" message/role: "assistant" message/stopReason: "toolUse" message/timestamp: 1773799758285 message/usage/cacheRead: 35072 message/usage/cacheWrite: 0 message/usage/cost/cacheRead: 0 message/usage/cost/cacheWrite: 0 message/usage/cost/input: 0 message/usage/cost/output: 0 message/usage/cost/total: 0 message/usage/input: 352 message/usage/output: 67 message/usage/totalTokens: 35491 parentId: "c1426239" timestamp: "2026-03-18T02:09:21.733Z" type: "message" wp_src_key: "file_1" access_source: "../openclaw/target_data/raw_log.dat" }
{ wp_event_id: 443603477540769490 id: "39638844" message/content[0]/text: "🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — Claws out, commit in—let's ship something mildly responsible.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts setup\n                       wizard.\n  configure            Interactive setup wizard for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files" message/content[0]/type: "text" message/details/aggregated: "🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.13 (61d171a) — Claws out, commit in—let's ship something mildly responsible.\n\nUsage: openclaw [options] [command]\n\nOptions:\n  --dev                Dev profile: isolate state under ~/.openclaw-dev, default\n                       gateway port 19001, and shift derived ports\n                       (browser/canvas)\n  -h, --help           Display help for command\n  --log-level <level>  Global log level override for file + console\n                       (silent|fatal|error|warn|info|debug|trace)\n  --no-color           Disable ANSI colors\n  --profile <name>     Use a named profile (isolates\n                       OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR/OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH under\n                       ~/.openclaw-<name>)\n  -V, --version        output the version number\n\nCommands:\n  Hint: commands suffixed with * have subcommands. Run <command> --help for details.\n  acp *                Agent Control Protocol tools\n  agent                Run one agent turn via the Gateway\n  agents *             Manage isolated agents (workspaces, auth, routing)\n  approvals *          Manage exec approvals (gateway or node host)\n  backup *             Create and verify local backup archives for OpenClaw\n                       state\n  browser *            Manage OpenClaw's dedicated browser (Chrome/Chromium)\n  channels *           Manage connected chat channels (Telegram, Discord, etc.)\n  clawbot *            Legacy clawbot command aliases\n  completion           Generate shell completion script\n  config *             Non-interactive config helpers\n                       (get/set/unset/file/validate). Default: starts setup\n                       wizard.\n  configure            Interactive setup wizard for credentials, channels,\n                       gateway, and agent defaults\n  cron *               Manage cron jobs via the Gateway scheduler\n  daemon *             Gateway service (legacy alias)\n  dashboard            Open the Control UI with your current token\n  devices *            Device pairing + token management\n  directory *          Lookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for\n                       supported chat channels\n  dns *                DNS helpers for wide-area discovery (Tailscale + CoreDNS)\n  docs                 Search the live OpenClaw docs\n  doctor               Health checks + quick fixes for the gateway and channels\n  gateway *            Run, inspect, and query the WebSocket Gateway\n  health               Fetch health from the running gateway\n  help                 Display help for command\n  hooks *              Manage internal agent hooks\n  logs                 Tail gateway file logs via RPC\n  memory *             Search and reindex memory files" message/details/cwd: "/Users/zuowenjian/.openclaw/workspace" message/details/durationMs: 1354 message/details/exitCode: 0 message/details/status: "completed" message/isError: false message/role: "toolResult" message/timestamp: 1773799763091 message/toolCallId: "tool_k03eV85usHu4Nijw70TBfIKD" message/toolName: "exec" parentId: "6f061cea" timestamp: "2026-03-18T02:09:23.092Z" type: "message" wp_src_key: "file_1" access_source: "../openclaw/target_data/raw_log.dat" }
{ wp_event_id: 443603477540769491 id: "eafc984e" message/api: "anthropic-messages" message/content[0]/thinking: "让我继续查看更多命令..." message/content[0]/thinkingSignature: "" message/content[0]/type: "thinking" message/content[1]/arguments/command: "openclaw --help 2>&1 | tail -30" message/content[1]/id: "tool_sUJgeQni9PYOSejgKQTqzuug" message/content[1]/name: "exec" message/content[1]/type: "toolCall" message/model: "k2p5" message/provider: "kimi-coding" message/role: "assistant" message/stopReason: "toolUse" message/timestamp: 1773799763093 message/usage/cacheRead: 35328 message/usage/cacheWrite: 0 message/usage/cost/cacheRead: 0 message/usage/cost/cacheWrite: 0 message/usage/cost/input: 0 message/usage/cost/output: 0 message/usage/cost/total: 0 message/usage/input: 723 message/usage/output: 37 message/usage/totalTokens: 36088 parentId: "39638844" timestamp: "2026-03-18T02:09:25.477Z" type: "message" wp_src_key: "file_1" access_source: "../openclaw/target_data/raw_log.dat" }
{ wp_event_id: 443603477540769492 id: "cec453c1" message/content[0]/text: "skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \\"Hi\\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \\"Run summary\\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \\"Hi\\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli" message/content[0]/type: "text" message/details/aggregated: "skills *             List and inspect available skills\n  status               Show channel health and recent session recipients\n  system *             System events, heartbeat, and presence\n  tui                  Open a terminal UI connected to the Gateway\n  uninstall            Uninstall the gateway service + local data (CLI remains)\n  update *             Update OpenClaw and inspect update channel status\n  webhooks *           Webhook helpers and integrations\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw models --help\n    Show detailed help for the models command.\n  openclaw channels login --verbose\n    Link personal WhatsApp Web and show QR + connection logs.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \\"Hi\\" --json\n    Send via your web session and print JSON result.\n  openclaw gateway --port 18789\n    Run the WebSocket Gateway locally.\n  openclaw --dev gateway\n    Run a dev Gateway (isolated state/config) on ws://127.0.0.1:19001.\n  openclaw gateway --force\n    Kill anything bound to the default gateway port, then start it.\n  openclaw gateway ...\n    Gateway control via WebSocket.\n  openclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \\"Run summary\\" --deliver\n    Talk directly to the agent using the Gateway; optionally send the WhatsApp reply.\n  openclaw message send --channel telegram --target @mychat --message \\"Hi\\"\n    Send via your Telegram bot.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli" message/details/cwd: "/Users/zuowenjian/.openclaw/workspace" message/details/durationMs: 1358 message/details/exitCode: 0 message/details/status: "completed" message/isError: false message/role: "toolResult" message/timestamp: 1773799766839 message/toolCallId: "tool_sUJgeQni9PYOSejgKQTqzuug" message/toolName: "exec" parentId: "eafc984e" timestamp: "2026-03-18T02:09:26.839Z" type: "message" wp_src_key: "file_1" access_source: "../openclaw/target_data/raw_log.dat" }
